1 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES - FLOOR VERSION
2 STATE OF OKLAHOMA
3 2nd Session of the 60th Legislature (2026)
4 HOUSE BILL 4140 By: Manger of the House
5 and
6 Hines of the Senate
7
8 AS INTRODUCED
9 An Act relating to crimes and punishments; amending
21 O.S. 2021, Sections 1705, as last amended by
10 Section 247, Chapter 486, O.S.L. 2025 and 1713, as
amended by Section 249, Chapter 486, O.S.L. 2025 (21
11 O.S. Supp. 2025, Section 1713), (21 O.S. Supp. 2025,
Sections 1705 and 1713), which relate to grand
12 larceny and receiving stolen property; modifying
elements of grand larceny and receiving stolen
13 property; and providing an effective date.
14
15
16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
17 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 21 O.S. 2021, Section 1705, as
18 last amended by Section 247, Chapter 486, O.S.L. 2025 (21 O.S. Supp.
19 2025, Section 1705), is amended to read as follows:
20 Section 1705. A. Grand larceny is a felony punishable as
21 follows:
22 1. If the value of the property is less than One Thousand
23 Dollars ($1,000.00), the person shall be punished by imprisonment in
24 the county jail for a term not to exceed one (1) year or by
HB4140 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 inca rceration in the county jail for one or more nights or weekends
2 pursuant to Section 991a-2 of Title 22 of the Oklahoma Statutes, at
3 the option of the court, or by a fine not to exceed One Thousand
4 Dollars ($1,000.00), or by both such imprisonment and fine;
5 2. If the property is one or more firearms, the property is
6 taken from the person of another, or the value of the property is
7 One Thousand Dollars ($1,000.00) or more but less than Two Thousand
8 Five Hundred Dollars ($2,500.00), the person shall be guilty of a
9 Class D3 felony offense and shall be punished by imprisonment as
10 provided for in subsections B through F of Section 20P of this
11 title, or by a fine not to exceed Two Thousand Five Hundred Dollars
12 ($2,500.00), or by both such imprisonment and fine;
13 3. In the event the value of the property is Two Thousand Five
14 Hundred Dollars ($2,500.00) or more but less than Fifteen Thousand
15 Dollars ($15,000.00), the person shall be guilty of a Class D1
16 felony offense and shall be punished by imprisonment as provided for
17 in subsections B through F of Section 20N of this title, or by a
18 fine not to exceed One Thousand Dollars ($1,000.00), or by both such
19 imprisonment and fine; or
20 4. If the property is one or more firearms or the value of the
21 property is Fifteen Thousand Dollars ($15,000.00) or more, the
22 person shall be guilty of a Class C2 felony offense and shall be
23 punished by imprisonment as provided for in subsections B through F
24
HB4140 HFLR Page 2
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 of S ection 20M of this title, or by a fine not to exceed One
2 Thousand Dollars ($1,000.00), or by both such imprisonment and fine.
3 B. The person shall also be ordered to pay restitution to the
4 victim as provided in Section 991f of Title 22 of the Oklahoma
5 Statutes.
6 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 21 O.S. 2021, Section 1713, as
7 amended by Section 249, Chapter 486, O.S.L. 2025 (21 O.S. Supp.
8 2024, Section 1713), is amended to read as follows:
9 Section 1713. A. Every person who buys or receives, in any
10 manner, upon any consideration, personal property of a value of One
11 Thousand Dollars ($1,000.00) or more that has been stolen,
12 embezzled, obtained by false pretense or robbery, knowing or having
13 reasonable cause to believe the same to have been stolen, embezzled,
14 obtained by false pretense, or robbery, or who conceals, withholds,
15 or aids in concealing or withholding such property from the owner
16 shall, upon conviction, be guilty of a felony punishable as follows:
17 1. If the value of the personal property is One Thousand
18 Dollars ($1,000.00) or more but less than Two Thousand Five Hundred
19 Dollars ($2,500.00), the person shall be guilty of a Class D3 felony
20 offense and shall be punished by imprisonment as provided for in
21 subsections B through F of Section 20P of this title, or by a fine
22 not to exceed Five Hundred Dollars ($500.00), or by both such fine
23 and imprisonment;
24
HB4140 HFLR Page 3
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 2. If the value of the personal property is Two Thousand Five
2 Hundred Dollars ($2,500.00) or more but less than Fifteen Thousand
3 Dollars ($15,000.00), the person shall be guilty of a Class D1
4 felony offense and shall be punished by imprisonment as provided for
5 in subsections B through F of Section 20N of this title, or by a
6 fine not to exceed Five Hundred Dollars ($500.00), or by both such
7 fine and imprisonment; or
8 3. If the property is one or more firearms or the value of the
9 personal property is Fifteen Thousand Dollars ($15,000.00) or more,
10 the person shall be guilty of a Class C2 felony offense and shall be
11 punished by imprisonment as provided for in subsections B through F
12 of Section 20M of this title, or by a fine not to exceed Five
13 Hundred Dollars ($500.00), or by both such imprisonment and fine.
14 B. If the personal property that has been stolen, embezzled,
15 obtained by false pretense or robbery has a value of less than One
16 Thousand Dollars ($1,000.00), the person shall, upon conviction, be
17 guilty of a misdemeanor punishable by imprisonment in the county
18 jail for a term not to exceed six (6) months.
19 C. Every person who, without making reasonable inquiry, buys,
20 receives, conceals, withholds, or aids in concealing or withholding
21 any property which has been stolen, embezzled, obtained by false
22 pretense or robbery, or otherwise feloniously obtained, under such
23 circumstances as should cause such person to make reasonable inquiry
24 to ascertain that the person from whom such property was bought or
HB4140 HFLR Page 4
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 rece ived had the legal right to sell or deliver it shall be presumed
2 to have bought or received such property knowing it to have been so
3 stolen or wrongfully obtained. This presumption may, however, be
4 rebutted by proof.
5 SECTION 3. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
6
7 COMMITTEE REPORT BY: COMMITTEE ON JUDICIARY AND PUBLIC SAFETY
